    <h1>Order confirmation</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Send order confirmations for incoming orders to your customers. In plentymarkets, you can generate order confirmations as PDF files, for example if you want to print them or send them to your customers as an email attachment.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Setting up a document template for order confirmations</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Before generating order confirmations, you have to set up a document template. Go to <strong>Setup » Client » <em>Select client</em> » Locations » <em>Select location</em> » Documents » Order confirmation</strong> to set up the template.<br>
Further information and instructions on setting up the document template are available on the <a href="/en/orders/order-documents">Order documents</a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="200">2. Generating a single order confirmation</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can generate order confirmations directly in an order. To do so, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Generating a single order confirmation:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Orders » Edit orders</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Order overview</strong> opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Use the filters to search (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span>) for the order for which you want to generate an order confirmation.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the required order.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Go to the <strong>Receipts</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the document <strong>Order confirmation</strong> from the <strong>Create receipt</strong> drop-down list.<br></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to <a href="#table-generate-order-confirmation">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings to generate the order confirmation.<br>
→ A <strong>PDF file</strong> of the just generated order confirmation opens.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
